  • Read in subject 1 in the dataset and calculate the sum of the level 1 type 1 volumes
df <- "~/Downloads/DataScience/Assignment3/data/"
fileList <- dir(df)
dat <- readSubject(paste(df, fileList[1], sep = "")) %>% 
  subject2df()

dat <- filter(dat, type == 1, level == 1)
sum(dat$volume)
## [1] 1378295
  • The sum of the volume is 1378295

  • Read in the file from github
q2 <- read.table("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bcaffo/ds4ph-bme/master/data/classInterests.txt", header = T)
  • Creat bar plots for year and program
library(ggplot2)

# for year
ggplot(q2, aes(Year)) + geom_bar()

# for program
ggplot(q2, aes(Program)) + geom_bar()

  • Mosaic plot
devtools::install_github("haleyjeppson/ggmosaic")
## Skipping install of 'ggmosaic' from a github remote, the SHA1 (7307d643) has not changed since last install.
##   Use `force = TRUE` to force installation
library(ggmosaic)

ggplot(data = q2) +
   geom_mosaic(aes(x = product(Year, Program), fill=Year), na.rm=TRUE) +
   labs(x = "Year ", y = "Program")

Question 4

  • Read in the file
q4 <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jhu-advdatasci/2018/master/data/GSE5859_exprs.csv")
  • Get the demeaned matrix
q4 <- select(q4, -X)

#calculate column mean and row mean
col <- colMeans(q4)
row <- rowMeans(q4)

#-colmean
q4 <- sweep(q4, 2, col)
#-rowmean
q4 <- sweep(q4, 1, row)

Question 5&6

  • Question 5: Plot health spending verse year colored by state
q5 <- read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/jhu-advdatasci/2018/master/data/KFF/healthcare-spending.csv",
               skip = 2)

#delete rows of notes
q5 <- q5[-(53:61),]

#change the data into long format
q5_long <- gather(q5, year, health_spending, 
                  X1991__Total.Health.Spending:X2014__Total.Health.Spending, factor_key=TRUE)

#plot
a <- (1991:2014)
ggplot(q5_long, aes(x=q5_long$year, y=q5_long$health_spending)) + 
  geom_point(aes(colour=Location), 
             size=0.8) +
  labs(y = "Total Health Spending", x = "Year") +
  scale_x_discrete(labels= a) +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1),
        legend.title = element_text(size = 8), 
        legend.text = element_text(size = 6))

  • Question 6: Create a barplot of average health care spending by state.
q5$mean <- rowMeans(q5[,-1])

ggplot(q5, aes(x=q5$Location, y=q5$mean)) + 
  geom_col() +
  labs(x = "State", y = "Average Health Spending") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1))
